ps 
ps -a - shows only user define process
ps -e shows all process in user and system 
ps -f full format info with detail
ps -elf  (all p)
ps -l long list 
ps -aux all process in wide format 
ppid parent process id
pid process id
NI nice (range is -20 to 20)
ps -axjf shows child process also tree diagram (x is to remove terminal)
sleep command used to frize system for some time ex sleep 30 system will sleep for 30sec
& sign will run process in background 
jobs command 


top command shows all process running as well as stop(real time process)
htop (it also shows full info)
running 
stopped
